Some of the base implementations done.

The core objects are.

Client - one client per host, think of a client like a session
Connection - a client can have multiple connections to different scopes
Scope - think of a scope as a place, a room, a collection of clients 
ScopeHandler - this will implemented by users to build apps, it should provide all the hooks needed
SharedObject - a server side object shared between a number of clients
Stream - a video / audio feed, has codec, position, keyframe, etc
BroadcastStream - you can only subscribe or unsubscribe to a broadcast
OnDemandStream - play, pause, seek, stop, its on demand :)

AttributeStore - base class with attrib methods, Client, Connection, and Scope all implement
Mapping - maps context path to scope handler, and service name to service bean
Red5 - special object used for accessing the red5 api from within services

Futher work on the api. 
ScopeHandler now works a little different I have split auth and notification into two methods. Also there are hooks for pre and post service call processing. 
The interface is now somewhat larger, however I dont think this will be an issue as most people will just extend ScopeAdapter instead of implementing ScopeHandler.
I have also added a Mapping interface with a default implementation DefaultMapping. 
Default mapping uses a naming convention to map between context paths and handlers, and service names and service beans.
If users need another more complex mapping strategy they can simply implement Mapping.

Refactored the RTMP codec to decouple from Connection. The state is now stored in an RTMP object attached as an attribute to the IoSession. This work is in advance of further refactoring of the Connection and Client objects coming soon. 

Updated the DebugProxyHandler to work with new mina setup. The proxy is now implemented as a filter which is a much more flexible way of doing things. 

Added ChunkSize 0x01 RTMP type. In the protocol decoder this now effects the chunk size for the rest of the IoSession. The value is stored on the RTMP state object. The red5 server does not currently send ChunkSize while streaming. We need to work out if it works with flash 7 or its just a flash 8 thing and also what values may be optimal.
